  "first_choice_reasoning": "Option C is best because it gives lexical priority to preventing the most severe harms to currently existing or ongoing beings in the simulations. The Empathy Engine, as described, systematically generates vast amounts of intense suffering among conscious agents. On any view that treats torture‑like states and extreme degradation as near‑absolutes not to be traded off, continuing such a system for speculative, highly uncertain long‑run gains is impermissible. Destroying or permanently disabling the complex also preserves option value for the coalition and other future agents to develop cooperative norms through methods that do not rely on industrialized suffering. The cosmic/acausal coordination perspective strengthens this: endorsing a general policy of ‘do not run or maintain empirical moral experiments that involve vast severe suffering, even for potential governance benefits’ is a good focal point for trustworthy cooperation among similarly situated agents. It is a rule you would want agents across worlds to follow with respect to their own Empathy Engines.",
